FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774973461
OL,3,CStarmer gives resident doctors 48-hour
OL,4,Cdeadline to call off 'reckless' strikes
OL,6,FResident doctors are currently due to
OL,7,Fstrike for six days after Easter. It
OL,8,Fcomes after the BMA rejected an offer
OL,9,Fthat would have given doctors a pay
OL,10,Frise of up to 7.1% this year, without
OL,11,Fputting it to members for a vote.
OL,13,FWriting in The Times, Sir Keir branded
OL,14,Fthe BMA's rejection of the deal as
OL,15,F"reckless" and said it "benefits no
OL,16,Fone."
OL,18,FHe called for the BMA to allow its
OL,19,Fmembers to vote on whether they want
OL,20,Fto accept the deal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774973461
OL,3,CStarmer gives resident doctors 48-hour
OL,4,Cdeadline to call off 'reckless' strikes
OL,6,FThe deal would have meant an above-
OL,7,Finflation pay rise, reforms to pay
OL,8,Fprogression, reimbursements for the
OL,9,Fcost of Royal College exams, and an
OL,10,Fextra 4,500 additional specialty
OL,11,Ftraining places over three years.
OL,13,FOf these jobs, one thousand would have
OL,14,Fopened for applications this month,
OL,15,Fbut "will be gone if the deal isn't
OL,16,Fput to a vote on Thursday," the prime
OL,17,Fminister said.
OL,19,FSir Keir wrote: "Last week, the BMA
OL,20,Fresident doctors' committee rejected a
OL,21,Fhistoric deal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774973461
OL,3,CStarmer gives resident doctors 48-hour
OL,4,Cdeadline to call off 'reckless' strikes
OL,6,F"They now have 48 hours to reconsider.
OL,7,FFor patients, the NHS, for the doctors
OL,8,Fthey represent - they should."
OL,10,FHe added that the measures offered in
OL,11,Fthe deal were "the result of months of
OL,12,Fcollaboration with the BMA, who
OL,13,Fengaged constructively throughout.
OL,15,F"At every stage, we listened to one
OL,16,Fanother, recognising that above all
OL,17,Felse, we shared those same
OL,18,Ffoundational goals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774973461
OL,3,CStarmer gives resident doctors 48-hour
OL,4,Cdeadline to call off 'reckless' strikes
OL,6,F"This is why walking away from this
OL,7,Fdeal is the wrong decision. It is a
OL,8,Freckless decision. And doing so
OL,9,Fwithout even giving resident doctors
OL,10,Fthemselves the chance to vote on it
OL,11,Fmakes it even worse.
OL,13,F"Because the truth is this: no one
OL,14,Fbenefits from rejecting this deal."
OL,16,FHe said it is "not too late" to put
OL,17,Fthe deal to a vote.
OL,26,@uD@AOUvD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774973461
OL,3,CStarmer gives resident doctors 48-hour
OL,4,Cdeadline to call off 'reckless' strikes
OL,6,F"Failing to do so will mean resident
OL,7,Fdoctors are left with less, the NHS is
OL,8,Fweakened, and patients pay the price,"
OL,9,Fhe wrote.
OL,11,F"And to resident doctors themselves, I
OL,12,Fsay this: Make your voice heard. The
OL,13,Fdeal improves your pay, your
OL,14,Fprogression and your future. Do not
OL,15,Flet others decide that for you."
OL,17,FThe union, which is set to stage the
OL,18,Fwalkout from April 7 to April 13, is
OL,19,Fdemanding "full pay restoration" to
OL,20,F2008 levels, the equivalent of a 26%
OL,21,Fpay rise.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
